<c74object name='fluid.noveltyslice~' category='FluidCorpusManipulation'>
	<digest>Realtime Novelty-Based Slicer</digest>
	<description>A realtime slicer using an algorithm assessing novelty in the signal to estimate the slicing points.</description>
  <discussion>
    <h4><openfilelink filename="Fluid Corpus Manipulation Toolkit.maxpat">Open the Overview Patch</openfilelink></h4>
            <p>A novelty curve is derived from running a kernel across the diagonal of the similarity matrix, and looking for peaks of changes. It implements the algorithm published in 'Automatic Audio Segmentation Using a Measure of Audio Novelty' by J Foote.</p>
        <p>The process will return an audio stream with single sample impulses at estimated starting points of the different slices.</p>

    <p>Read more about fluid.noveltyslice~ on the <a href='https://learn.flucoma.org/reference/noveltyslice'>learn platform</a>.</p>
    <p>fluid.noveltyslice~ is part of the Fluid Decomposition Toolkit of the FluCoMa project. For more explanations, learning material, and discussions on its musicianly uses, visit <a href="http://www.flucoma.org/">flucoma.org</a>.</p>
  </discussion>
	<!--METADATA-->
	<metadatalist>
		<metadata name='author'>FluCoMa</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Fluid Decomposition</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>corpus</metadata>
	</metadatalist>
	<!--ARGUMENTS-->
	<objarglist>
      <objarg name='kernelsize' optional='1' type='number'>
        <digest>
              KernelSize
        </digest>
        <description>
              <p>Shorthand argument for <m>kernelsize</m></p>

          <!--  -->
        </description>
        <attributelist>
          <attribute name="default" get="1" set="1" type="int" size='1' value='3' />
        </attributelist>
      </objarg>
      <objarg name='filtersize' optional='1' type='number'>
        <digest>
              Smoothing Filter Size
        </digest>
        <description>
              <p>Shorthand argument for <m>filtersize</m></p>

          <!--  -->
        </description>
        <attributelist>
          <attribute name="default" get="1" set="1" type="int" size='1' value='1' />
        </attributelist>
      </objarg>
	</objarglist>
	<!--MESSAGES-->
  <methodlist><method name="reset">
      <arglist />
      <digest>
        Return the object to its original state
      </digest>
      <description>
        Calling <m>reset</m> will change parameter values back to those the object was <i>created</i> with, i.e. any attribute values set in the box will be retained
      </description>
    </method></methodlist>
	<!--ATTRIBUTES-->
	<attributelist><attribute name='algorithm' get='1' set='1' type='int' size='1'>
        <digest>
              Algorithm for Feature Extraction
        </digest>
        <description>
              <p>The feature on which novelty is computed.</p>

          
        </description><attributelist><attribute name="default" get="1" set="1" type="int" size='1' value='0' /><attribute name="enumvals" get="1" set="1" type="atom" size='5'>
            <enumlist><enum name='0'>
                <description>
                      <p>Spectrum - The magnitude of the full spectrum.</p>

                </description>
              </enum><enum name='1'>
                <description>
                      <p>MFCC - 13 Mel-Frequency Cepstrum Coefficients.</p>

                </description>
              </enum><enum name='2'>
                <description>
                      <p>Chroma - The contour of a 12-band chromagram.</p>

                </description>
              </enum><enum name='3'>
                <description>
                      <p>Pitch - The pitch and its confidence.</p>

                </description>
              </enum><enum name='4'>
                <description>
                      <p>Loudness - The true peak and loudness.</p>

                </description>
              </enum></enumlist>
          </attribute></attributelist></attribute><attribute name='fftsettings' get='1' set='1' type='int' size='4'>
        <digest>
              FFT Settings
        </digest>
        <description>
              <p>FFT settings consist of three numbers representing the window size, hop size and FFT size in samples:</p>
    <p>The hop size and fft size can both be set to -1 (and are by default), with slightly different meanings:</p>
    <ul class="simple">
    <li>For the hop size, -1 = <m>windowsize/2</m></li>
    <li>For the FFT size, -1 = <m>windowsize</m> snapped to the nearest equal / greater power of 2 (e.g. <m>windowsize 1024</m> =&gt; <m>fftsize 1024</m>, but <m>windowssize 1000</m> also =&gt; <m>fftsize 1024</m>)</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Constraints</strong></p>
    <ul class="simple">
    <li>FFTSize, if != -1, will snap to the next greatest power of two &amp;gt; 4</li>
    <li>The maximum FFT size is limited to the value of the <m>maxfftsize</m> argument</li>
    <li>if FFT size != -1, then window size is clipped at FFT size</li>
    </ul>

          
        </description><attributelist><attribute name="default" get="1" set="1" type="int" size='4' value='[[&#39;winSize&#39;, 1024], [&#39;hopSize&#39;, -1], [&#39;fftSize&#39;, -1]]' /></attributelist></attribute><attribute name='filtersize' get='1' set='1' type='int' size='1'>
        <digest>
              Smoothing Filter Size
        </digest>
        <description>
              <p>The size (in hops) of a smoothing filter that is applied on the novelty curve. A larger filter size allows for cleaner cuts on very sharp changes.</p>
    <p><strong>Constraints</strong></p>
    <ul class="simple">
    <li>Minimum: <m>1</m></li>
    <li>Maximum: <m>maxfiltersize</m></li>
    </ul>

          
        </description><attributelist><attribute name="default" get="1" set="1" type="int" size='1' value='1' /></attributelist></attribute><attribute name='kernelsize' get='1' set='1' type='int' size='1'>
        <digest>
              KernelSize
        </digest>
        <description>
              <p>The granularity of the window in which the algorithm looks for change, in hops. A small number will be sensitive to short term changes, and a large number should look for long term changes.</p>
    <p><strong>Constraints</strong></p>
    <ul class="simple">
    <li>Minimum: <m>3</m></li>
    <li>Maximum: <m>maxkernelsize</m></li>
    <li>Snaps to odd numbers</li>
    </ul>

          
        </description><attributelist><attribute name="default" get="1" set="1" type="int" size='1' value='3' /></attributelist></attribute><attribute name='maxfftsize' get='1' set='1' type='int' size='1'>
        <digest>
              Maximum FFT Size
        </digest>
        <description>
              <p>Set an explicit upper bound on the FFT size at object instantiation. The default of -1 sets this to whatever the initial FFT size is</p>

          
        </description><attributelist><attribute name="default" get="1" set="1" type="int" size='1' value='-1' /></attributelist></attribute><attribute name='maxfiltersize' get='1' set='1' type='int' size='1'>
        <digest>
              Maximum Smoothing Filter Size
        </digest>
        <description>
              <p>Manually sets a maximum value for <m>filtersize</m>. Can only be set at object instantiation. The default of -1 sets this equal to the initial value of <m>filtersize</m></p>

          
        </description><attributelist><attribute name="default" get="1" set="1" type="int" size='1' value='-1' /></attributelist></attribute><attribute name='maxkernelsize' get='1' set='1' type='int' size='1'>
        <digest>
              Maximum KernelSize
        </digest>
        <description>
              <p>Manually sets a maximum value for <m>kernelsize</m>. Can only be set at object instantiation. The default of -1 sets this equal to the initial value of <m>kernelsize</m></p>

          
        </description><attributelist><attribute name="default" get="1" set="1" type="int" size='1' value='-1' /></attributelist></attribute><attribute name='minslicelength' get='1' set='1' type='int' size='1'>
        <digest>
              Minimum Length of Slice
        </digest>
        <description>
              <p>The minimum duration of a slice in number of hops.</p>
    <p><strong>Constraints</strong></p>
    <ul class="simple">
    <li>Minimum: <m>0</m></li>
    </ul>

          
        </description><attributelist><attribute name="default" get="1" set="1" type="int" size='1' value='2' /></attributelist></attribute><attribute name='threshold' get='1' set='1' type='float64' size='1'>
        <digest>
              Threshold
        </digest>
        <description>
              <p>The normalised threshold, between 0 and 1, on the novelty curve to consider it a segmentation point.</p>
    <p><strong>Constraints</strong></p>
    <ul class="simple">
    <li>Minimum: <m>0</m></li>
    </ul>

          
        </description><attributelist><attribute name="default" get="1" set="1" type="int" size='1' value='0.5' /></attributelist></attribute><attribute name='warnings' get='1' set='1' type='int' size='1'>
        <digest>
              Warnings
        </digest>
        <description>
              <p>Enable warnings to be issued whenever a parameter value is constrained (e.g. clipped)</p>

          
        </description><attributelist><attribute name="default" get="1" set="1" type="int" size='1' value='0' /></attributelist></attribute></attributelist>
	<!--RELATED-->
	<seealsolist>
    <seealso name='fluid.bufnoveltyslice~' />    <seealso name='fluid.onsetslice~' />    <seealso name='fluid.ampslice~' />    <seealso name='fluid.transientslice~' /></seealsolist>
</c74object>